Emilio Aguinaldo was the first president of the Philippines. He led the country's revolution against Spanish colonial rule and fought against U.S. occupation. Manuel Quezon was the second president of the Philippines. He advocated for independence and helped establish the Commonwealth of the Philippines with self-governance under the U.S. Both presidents played pivotal roles in the Philippines' struggle for freedom and sovereignty.
